## Coding Conventions

- Markdown / MDX: use front matter for metadata (`title`, `description`, `sidebar_position`)
- Headings: H1 is the page title (from front matter); start content headings at H2
- Components: PascalCase filenames, 2-space indentation, TypeScript props interfaces
- CSS: use CSS custom properties for theming; scope component styles with CSS modules
- Links: use relative paths for internal links (not absolute URLs)
- Images: store in `static/img/` or co-located with docs; always include `alt` text
- Code blocks: always specify language for syntax highlighting

## Security Requirements

**Never read, display, or include the contents of these files:**

| Category | Files / Patterns |
|----------|-----------------|
| Environment | `.env`, `.env.*`, `.env.local`, `.env.production` — `.env.example` is safe |
| Keys & certs | `*.key`, `*.pem`, `*.p12`, `*.pfx` |
| Credentials | `credentials.json`, `*service-account*.json`, `auth.json` |
| Cloud auth | `.aws/credentials`, `.aws/config`, `.azure/` |
| SSH / Git | `.ssh/`, `.git-credentials`, `.netrc` |
| Secrets | `secrets.yml`, `vault.yml`, any file with `secret` or `token` in name |

**Hard rules:**
- `build/` and `node_modules/` are generated — never commit
- API keys used in `docusaurus.config.ts` (e.g., Algolia) must come from env vars
- Never include tokens or keys in committed configuration

